<paragraph xmlns:gate="http://www.gate.ac.uk" gate:gateId="0" gate:annotMaxId="285"><Location gate:gateId="225" rule1="Location1" locType="city" rule2="LocFinal">Adler</Location>, Kurt Herbert, opera conductor; <Event_Birth gate:gateId="284" RE="April 2, 1905" Pred="birth" Pred-tyoe="time"><Birth gate:gateId="282" predict="birth">b.</Birth> <Location gate:gateId="227" locType="city" rule1="Location1" gate:matches="227;230" rule2="LocFinal">Vienna</Location>, <Date gate:gateId="228" rule1="DateNameRev" kind="date" rule2="DateOnlyFinal">April 2, 1905</Date></Event_Birth>. He studied at the Vienna Cons.; was a theater conductor in <Location gate:gateId="230" locType="city" rule1="InLoc1" gate:matches="227;230" rule2="LocFinal">Vienna</Location> (<Date gate:gateId="231" rule1="TempYear3" kind="date" rule2="YearOnlyFinal">1925</Date>many. He served as assistant to Toscanini at the Salzburg Festival in <Date gate:gateId="233" rule1="YearContext1" kind="date" rule2="DateOnlyFinal">1936</Date>; then settled in the <Location gate:gateId="234" rule1="Location1" locType="country" rule2="LocFinal">U.S.</Location>; was with the Chicago Opera Company (<Date gate:gateId="236" rule1="TempYear3" kind="date" rule2="YearOnlyFinal">1938</Date>the staff of the San Francisco Opera; in <Date gate:gateId="238" rule1="YearContext1" kind="date" rule2="DateOnlyFinal">1953</Date> he became its artistic director. He is no relation to Kurt Adler (q.v.). </paragraph>